{
  "texts": [
    "Linguistic evidence suggested that European Tartary buckwheat is closely related to the Mongols.",
    "According to 'The History of The Mongol Empire', Tartary buckwheat spread to Europe with the expansion of the Mongol Empire.",
    "European historical data shows that Tartary buckwheat was introduced into Europe in the Middle Ages [21,22].",
    "A close phylogenetic relationship was found between accessions from northern China and outside China, indicating that Tartary buckwheat was introduced to Europe potentially only once from northern China [8].",
    "However, due to only a few accessions used in our analysis which came from outside China, this conclusion needs further verification."
  ]
}